  'alloc.alt.title': 'Technical alternatives before creating a new org',
  'alloc.alt.sub': 'In a landscape with many orgs, creating another one has direct cost (Full Copy, replicated Shield, licenses, DR, backup). Evaluate these options first:',
  'alloc.alt.dataCloud.title': 'Data Cloud as a logical tenant',
  'alloc.alt.dataCloud.processWants.enabled': 'The process already requires Data Cloud. One or more orgs already have Data Cloud enabled — consider allocating as a Data Space in that org instead of creating a new tenant.',
  'alloc.alt.dataCloud.processWants.notEnabled': 'The process already requires Data Cloud. Data Cloud is not yet enabled in any landscape org. Evaluate the cost of enabling + architecting as an identity hub.',
  'alloc.alt.dataCloud.generic': 'If the process needs to unify data across existing orgs (customer 360-degree view), Data Cloud solves it without creating a new CRM org. Read-heavy, with Data Actions for orchestrated writes.',
  'alloc.alt.2gp.title': 'Unlocked Package (2GP) in an existing org',
  'alloc.alt.2gp.enabled': '{count} landscape org(s) already use 2GP — modularize the process as an independent package, with its own release cadence, without a new Full Copy sandbox.',
  'alloc.alt.2gp.notEnabled': 'No landscape org adopts 2GP today. If DevOps maturity allows, adopting 2GP solves release autonomy without additional license cost — it is a prerequisite for modularizing inside single-org.',
  'alloc.alt.expCloud.title': 'Experience Cloud site + permission sets',
  'alloc.alt.expCloud.processWants.enabled': 'Process requires Experience Cloud. It already exists in one or more orgs — create a dedicated site with isolated permission sets in that org, instead of a new tenant.',
  'alloc.alt.expCloud.processWants.notEnabled': 'Process requires Experience Cloud. Enabling Experience Cloud in an existing org + permission sets solves UX isolation for partners/customers without creating a new CRM org.',
  'alloc.alt.expCloud.generic.title': 'Experience Cloud + permission sets',
  'alloc.alt.expCloud.generic': 'If the demand is to isolate UX or expose Setup to an external partner, an Experience Cloud site in an existing org solves it — isolated permission sets, controlled guest user.',
  'alloc.alt.mulesoft.title': 'MuleSoft as canonical layer',
  'alloc.alt.mulesoft.desc': 'If the process needs to orchestrate across orgs (e.g., enrich with master data from another BU), the cost belongs in MuleSoft/iPaaS, not in creating one more Salesforce org. Reduces coupling and avoids data duplication.',
  'alloc.alt.shared.title': 'Shared services / platform org',
  'alloc.alt.shared.desc': 'In landscapes with many orgs, there is typically a "platform" or corporate org that centralizes transverse capabilities (compliance, master data, lead management, integration). Check whether the process fits there before proposing a new org.',
  'alloc.sunset.title': 'If a new org: mandatory sunset plan (24 months)',
  'alloc.sunset.step1': '<strong>Formal justification:</strong> which blocker prevents reuse (regulator, data controller, irreversible feature, capacity).',
  'alloc.sunset.step2': '<strong>Executive sponsor:</strong> name + area. No sponsor, no opening.',
  'alloc.sunset.step3': '<strong>Consolidation deadline:</strong> 24 months after go-live. If permanent by nature, formalize it in the ARB — not as a default.',
  'alloc.sunset.step4': '<strong>Inter-party LGPD contract</strong> if the data controller differs.',
  'alloc.sunset.step5': '<strong>DR runbook + backup contract</strong> before go-live (not after).',
  'alloc.sunset.step6': '<strong>ADR published</strong> in Confluence/Git — "Process X went to a new org because...".',
  'alloc.sunset.step7': '<strong>Return to Topology Mode</strong> to decide the sub-topology (Hub-and-Spoke default, Federated only if bidirectional sync is unavoidable or transitional M&A).',

